newsitem.title: INDONESIA: Indonesia palm olein stable in late trade.
newsitem.headline: Indonesia palm olein stable in late trade.

text.p: Indonesian palm olein prices were mostly unchanged in late trading on Tuesday, traders said.
They said olein was quoted at 1,420-25 rupiah/kg in Jakarta, but trades were mostly at the lower end of the range.
Crude palm oil was last done at 1,223 rupiah/kg in the North Sumatran city of Medan on Monday.

"There was a bit of activity earlier in the day, but things have slowed down in the late afternoon," one trader said. "Gains in Malaysia in late trading today could help to lift local sentiment tomorrow."
Traders said there was virtually no margin between crude palm oil and olein, which could see players stepping up their exports of the raw material.
Data from Belawan Port showed that the MT Antea left the port on Sunday for Port Klang, Malaysia with 4,000 tonnes of crude palm oil.
The MT Vishnescky will leave for Port Klang on Wednesday with 1,200 tonnes of stearin. The MV Payao Navee will leave for Phuket on Dec 2 with 5,000 tonnes of palm kernel expeller.
The MT Mutiara will leave on Tuesday for Tanjung Priok with 2,000 tonnes of olein.
